[The "polio-free" status of Nigeria has been based on the interruption of WPV1 circulation and not cVDPV. Checking the records, the date of onset of most recent case of paralysis associated with cVDPV2 in Nigeria was 14 May 2021, hence it is premature to declare transmission interrupted. Note that Nigeria is one of the countries using the novel OPV2, which hopefully should reduce the likelihood of cVDPV2 cases occurring in the country. Time will tell.

Should the transmission of WPV1 be interrupted globally, one suspects the GPEI (Global Polio Eradication Initiative) and WHO, will revisit the definition of a polio-free world to address the cVDPV associated paralytic cases. An alternate media report from 5 Jul 2021 is available at https://thenationonlineng.net/fg-worried-over-outbreaks-of-vaccine-derived-polio-in-14-states/.

A map showing the states of Nigeria can be found at https://nigerianfinder.com/map-of-nigeria-states/. - Mod.MPP

